WEBVTT

00:02.020 --> 00:05.000
- <i>Previously on</i> Tyrant...
- Ahmed, Ahmed.

00:05.030 --> 00:06.030
I'm bleeding.

00:06.070 --> 00:08.400
...but we will
push them back.

00:08.430 --> 00:09.290
AHMED: Nusrat.

00:09.330 --> 00:12.470
Your wife is fine.

00:12.510 --> 00:14.560
The baby didn't make it.

00:15.340 --> 00:16.710
I'm asking you
as an Al Fayeed

00:16.740 --> 00:18.710
for the money that
my grandfather left to me.

00:18.740 --> 00:22.000
I will arrange to transfer money
to you from a Swiss account.

00:22.030 --> 00:22.950
Ten million.

00:22.980 --> 00:26.020
Then you go, you leave, Sam,
and don't come back again.

00:26.050 --> 00:28.180
I have a friend, Halima.

00:28.220 --> 00:32.250
She says that there's a growing
insurgency called the Red Hand.

00:32.290 --> 00:34.860
- Why are you telling me this?
- They need money.

00:34.890 --> 00:38.460
You have your bombing targets?
You need to act now.

00:38.490 --> 00:41.030
- Do you want to give us our targets?
- The outskirts of the city.

00:41.070 --> 00:42.760
Somewhere where
you're sure no one is.

00:43.200 --> 00:45.130
- Genius.
- I don't care if we don't kill

00:45.170 --> 00:46.630
a single member
of the Caliphate; I do not want

00:46.660 --> 00:48.990
reports of civilian deaths.
Do you understand?

00:51.210 --> 00:53.240
SAMIRA:
<i>Bassam! Stop!</i>

00:54.780 --> 00:56.210
I warned you,
I'll kill her.

00:56.240 --> 00:57.280
(grunts)

00:57.320 --> 00:59.100
Oh, my... my God.

00:59.140 --> 01:00.700
Oh, my God.

01:19.400 --> 01:22.200
Good morning.

01:22.240 --> 01:24.070
Morning.

01:26.140 --> 01:27.110
Hi.

01:27.140 --> 01:28.540
Hi.

01:28.580 --> 01:31.310
Uh...

01:31.340 --> 01:35.150
So...

01:35.180 --> 01:37.380
we, um...

01:37.420 --> 01:39.380
Drank Chinese whiskey.

01:39.420 --> 01:40.380
Mmm.

01:40.420 --> 01:42.390
And then?

01:42.420 --> 01:43.820
Mmm.

01:43.860 --> 01:45.490
We didn't...?

01:45.520 --> 01:46.920
No.

01:49.530 --> 01:52.420
I don't really know
how to do this.

01:53.360 --> 01:55.300
That's okay.

01:56.630 --> 01:59.450
There's no rule book
for these kind of things.

02:01.410 --> 02:05.340
I'm gonna think the last time
I went on a date, I was 20.

02:05.380 --> 02:07.140
Oh, that's
what this was?

02:07.180 --> 02:09.150
No.

02:09.180 --> 02:11.080
I don't know.

02:11.080 --> 02:12.480
I think sleeping

02:12.520 --> 02:14.540
in all my clothes
on a first date

02:14.580 --> 02:16.320
sends the right message.

02:16.350 --> 02:18.720
Says I'm a good time,
but I'm in no hurry.

02:18.750 --> 02:20.820
(laughs)

02:20.860 --> 02:23.300
Whatever this is,

02:23.330 --> 02:26.090
we'll have time to figure it out
when we get home.

02:27.330 --> 02:30.370
We're really going home.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.400
That sounds good.

02:44.150 --> 02:46.150
(cell phone rings)

02:48.480 --> 02:50.450
(clears throat)

02:50.490 --> 02:51.920
Hey, honey.

02:53.390 --> 02:54.750
Hello?

02:54.790 --> 02:56.190
Sammy?

02:56.220 --> 02:57.620
Hi.

02:59.390 --> 03:01.290
I need to tell you something.

03:01.330 --> 03:02.700
What's wrong?

03:02.730 --> 03:03.340
Nothing.

03:03.380 --> 03:05.330
I'm-I'm fine.

03:05.370 --> 03:07.300
Um, but I'm not coming back.

03:07.330 --> 03:08.870
Not-not right now.
I-I just need to...

03:08.900 --> 03:11.000
W-W-Wait, what do you mean,
you're not coming back?

03:11.040 --> 03:13.650
There's a man inside Ma'an
who's fighting the Caliphate,

03:13.680 --> 03:16.040
and his name's Khalil.

03:16.080 --> 03:18.910
He needs money.

03:20.710 --> 03:22.080
I'm giving him my money,

03:22.120 --> 03:24.440
or as much of it as he can use.

03:24.480 --> 03:25.230
What?

03:25.270 --> 03:27.190
I'm just going there,
making sure it's him,

03:27.220 --> 03:28.690
and then I'll be right back.

03:28.720 --> 03:29.990
Sammy, listen to me.

03:30.020 --> 03:32.790
They killed Abdul.

03:32.840 --> 03:36.120
Threw him off a building
with eight other gay men.

03:37.160 --> 03:39.400
If I lived here,
it could have been me.

03:39.430 --> 03:40.820
But you don't live here, honey.

03:40.850 --> 03:42.510
You're an American kid
with money.

03:42.540 --> 03:44.300
Which is why I'm doing this.

03:44.340 --> 03:46.340
How are you even getting there?

03:46.370 --> 03:49.310
Abdul's friend
is taking me.

03:49.340 --> 03:51.310
Abdul's friend?

03:51.340 --> 03:52.950
Look, I know I'm taking a risk.

03:52.980 --> 03:54.130
Do you?

03:54.160 --> 03:56.180
What if he turns around
and holds you hostage?

03:56.210 --> 03:58.750
Then pay him.

03:58.780 --> 03:59.750
(phone beeps)

03:59.780 --> 04:01.720
Sammy...

04:07.060 --> 04:08.420
Who was that?

04:08.460 --> 04:10.880
Um, it was my lawyer.

04:17.529 --> 04:21.370
MARWAN: Black market traders
used these tunnels

04:21.399 --> 04:24.510
to avoid paying taxes
on goods in and out of Ma'an.

04:24.540 --> 04:28.080
The regime plugged most of them,
but they never found this one.

04:28.110 --> 04:30.340
(Sammy coughs violently)

04:33.980 --> 04:35.780
How can you breathe
down here, man?

04:35.820 --> 04:37.190
Ah, yeah. I...

04:37.220 --> 04:39.020
(coughs)

04:39.050 --> 04:40.790
(groans)

04:40.820 --> 04:43.810
There are other ways to
get your money to Khalil.

04:45.690 --> 04:47.690
I want to meet him.

04:49.200 --> 04:51.190
Okay, keep pressure
on the wound.

04:51.220 --> 04:52.870
(distant artillery fires)

04:52.900 --> 04:54.730
(explosion crashes)

04:56.670 --> 04:58.100
SIDDIQ: We just
lost two fighters.

04:58.130 --> 04:59.470
Did someone follow
you back here?

04:59.510 --> 05:01.160
- It's not the Caliphate.
- How do you know?

05:01.200 --> 05:03.680
They wouldn't attack us from the
air; they'd use ground forces.

05:03.710 --> 05:05.980
This is the government... they
must have spotted us flying over

05:06.010 --> 05:07.340
and mistaken us
for the Caliphate.

05:07.380 --> 05:08.280
Well, who are you calling?

05:08.320 --> 05:10.120
(explosion crashes)

05:12.560 --> 05:13.560
_

05:13.690 --> 05:15.080
_

05:15.420 --> 05:16.840
_

05:17.160 --> 05:19.270
_

05:20.860 --> 05:24.300
God in Heaven,
are you listening?

05:24.350 --> 05:26.540
Are you there?

05:28.120 --> 05:30.420
Is someone who has done
what I've done

05:30.470 --> 05:33.020
even allowed to pray to you?

05:34.740 --> 05:37.540
I don't know what to do.

05:37.580 --> 05:40.380
I can't bring my brother back.

05:40.410 --> 05:43.060
And there's not
enough rain in Abuddin

05:43.090 --> 05:46.370
to wash the blood from my hands.

05:48.420 --> 05:51.220
Am I being punished?

05:51.260 --> 05:53.640
I know I-I should be punished,

05:53.670 --> 05:57.480
but when does it end, and how?

05:58.730 --> 06:01.460
You want half my country?

06:01.500 --> 06:02.720
Take it.

06:02.750 --> 06:04.300
My grandson?

06:04.330 --> 06:06.170
You have him.

06:06.200 --> 06:09.170
What more do you want?

06:09.210 --> 06:12.570
When have I paid enough?

06:12.610 --> 06:15.010
You want to take me, yes?

06:15.040 --> 06:17.410
Take me.

06:18.710 --> 06:21.830
Just don't take my son.

06:21.860 --> 06:22.850
Please.

06:22.900 --> 06:27.040
Whatever you do,
don't take my son Ahmed.

06:28.960 --> 06:32.960
LEILA: You think praying
will solve our problems?

06:32.990 --> 06:35.430
We're dropping bombs in Ma'an.

06:35.430 --> 06:37.030
You have a war to run.

06:37.070 --> 06:38.770
This is my fault.

06:38.770 --> 06:40.270
For God's sake, Jamal.

06:40.300 --> 06:41.630
No, not in here.

06:41.670 --> 06:44.640
God has better things to do
than punish you.

06:51.580 --> 06:53.970
Whatever delusions you might
have about being punished

06:54.000 --> 06:55.380
you need to leave in here.

06:55.420 --> 06:58.950
You are the president of
Abuddin, commander in chief.

06:58.980 --> 07:02.320
Bassam betrayed you.

07:02.360 --> 07:03.320
Enough.

07:03.360 --> 07:05.760
(shouts in Arabic)

07:09.900 --> 07:11.970
RAMI:
<i>We're bombarding the northwest</i>

07:12.010 --> 07:15.800
outskirts of Ma'an,
beyond the 26th district.

07:15.830 --> 07:18.750
And here and here
along the western border.

07:18.790 --> 07:20.130
No man's land.

07:20.160 --> 07:22.040
An empty
industrial park.

07:22.070 --> 07:24.880
You wanted a victory.

07:24.910 --> 07:27.710
This is the best we could do
without killing civilians

07:27.760 --> 07:30.170
and turning the people
against us.

07:36.520 --> 07:39.920
The Caliphate is deeply embedded
in the local population.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.130
We can't make a plan
to retake the city

07:42.160 --> 07:44.330
until we have
proper intelligence.

07:44.360 --> 07:48.330
Mahmoud said he was developing
new assets inside Ma'an.

07:48.370 --> 07:50.370
Right, Solomon?

07:52.800 --> 07:55.170
He had a setback.

07:55.200 --> 07:56.810
One of Mahmoud's
informants

07:56.840 --> 07:59.340
turned out to be
a Caliphate plant.

07:59.380 --> 08:05.080
20 of his recruited assets
were executed late last night.

08:05.110 --> 08:07.950
Of course they were.

08:07.980 --> 08:13.660
A man can't win a war without
God being on his side.

08:13.690 --> 08:15.520
Without God?

08:19.840 --> 08:24.000
You are the only good news
I've had in a long time.

08:24.030 --> 08:26.690
An island in a
sea of troubles.

08:26.720 --> 08:29.040
I'm glad, Mr. President.

08:29.070 --> 08:31.470
You are my son.

08:31.510 --> 08:34.150
Call me Father.

08:40.960 --> 08:43.020
End this foolishness.

08:43.049 --> 08:46.620
Stop wasting good
bombs on bad targets.

08:50.120 --> 08:51.490
(bomb whistling)

08:51.530 --> 08:53.130
(shouting indistinctly)

08:55.930 --> 08:57.340
I need to talk to General Said.

08:57.380 --> 08:59.660
My name is Khalil.

08:59.700 --> 09:01.720
Yes, the same Khalil
who's fighting the Caliphate

09:01.750 --> 09:03.480
- inside Ma'an.
- (explosion crashes)

09:03.510 --> 09:06.480
You're not
targeting the Caliphate.

09:06.520 --> 09:08.750
You're hitting my fighters,
killing innocent people.

09:08.780 --> 09:11.290
You need to put me
through to General Said.

09:17.820 --> 09:19.150
What is it?

09:19.180 --> 09:20.700
(panting)

09:20.730 --> 09:24.720
Someone claiming to be Khalil
called the-the switchboard.

09:24.760 --> 09:25.990
He's on line three.

09:26.030 --> 09:28.130
Is he for real?

09:29.630 --> 09:31.230
He's on line three.

09:39.440 --> 09:41.200
Khalil, is it?

09:41.230 --> 09:43.410
This is General Said.

09:43.440 --> 09:45.300
General, you are
currently targeting

09:45.340 --> 09:47.950
your only potential allies
inside Ma'an.

09:47.980 --> 09:49.890
Your bombs just killed
three of my fighters

09:49.920 --> 09:51.780
and wounded another seven.

09:51.810 --> 09:52.680
And you expect me to believe

09:52.720 --> 09:54.870
you are who you claim
to be because...?

09:54.900 --> 09:58.010
I'm the one that broke
the Banu Zahra out of prison.

09:59.490 --> 10:00.910
That's public information.

10:00.940 --> 10:02.950
That doesn't mean you're Khalil.

10:04.690 --> 10:06.490
Okay, you want proof?

10:06.530 --> 10:08.130
I'll give you
a high-value target.

10:08.160 --> 10:09.520
Hit the northeast corner

10:09.550 --> 10:12.090
of Qusair Street and Idris.

10:16.810 --> 10:19.170
That is the residence
of the refinery manager.

10:19.210 --> 10:21.010
Not anymore.

10:21.040 --> 10:23.420
The Caliphate leadership
took it over.

10:25.740 --> 10:27.580
And you know this how?

10:28.250 --> 10:31.080
We conducted
reconnaissance.

10:31.120 --> 10:33.410
Abu Omar, Ihab Rashid...
all of them.

10:33.450 --> 10:37.390
That's where they are,
but I'm not sure for how long.

10:37.420 --> 10:40.260
General, I'm giving you
their headquarters.

10:40.320 --> 10:43.570
Or manipulating me
into killing civilians.

10:44.330 --> 10:47.030
You have to trust someone
on the ground inside Ma'an.

10:47.070 --> 10:48.670
Right now, you have no one.

10:48.700 --> 10:50.370
Otherwise, you wouldn't be
conducting bombing runs

10:50.410 --> 10:53.400
over empty industrial parks.

11:01.950 --> 11:03.980
I want to trust you.

11:04.020 --> 11:06.480
But I need something reliable.

11:06.520 --> 11:07.990
Proof.

11:08.020 --> 11:09.650
Like what?

11:09.690 --> 11:13.220
A Caliphate target.

11:13.260 --> 11:15.530
Tell me what
and when you're hitting it,

11:15.560 --> 11:17.490
and once it's reported
by a reliable source,

11:17.530 --> 11:20.260
then I'll know I can trust you.

11:20.300 --> 11:22.520
I'll be in touch.

11:23.870 --> 11:26.230
We could be missing the chance

11:26.270 --> 11:29.140
to decapitate their leadership.

11:29.180 --> 11:30.860
If we're wrong and we kill
innocent civilians,

11:30.900 --> 11:32.880
we're no better than they are.

11:32.910 --> 11:35.160
The people would
turn against us.

11:35.200 --> 11:37.910
Yes, it's a gamble.

11:37.950 --> 11:40.890
But shouldn't your father
be the one who decides

11:40.930 --> 11:43.520
if it's a gamble worth taking?

11:49.320 --> 11:51.610
Fine. I'll tell him.

11:53.930 --> 11:56.300
I need Munir to find us
another target.

11:56.330 --> 11:58.100
We may have an ally.

11:58.130 --> 12:00.370
You would work
with your brother?

12:03.870 --> 12:06.710
One devil at a time.

12:54.800 --> 12:59.430
Tyrant S02E08
"Fathers and Sons"

