13:15.870 --> 13:18.440
I keep thinking what
I could've done differently.

13:18.440 --> 13:19.580
No, this is not your fault.

13:19.580 --> 13:21.710
There must've been something.

13:21.750 --> 13:24.650
No one is blaming you.

13:24.680 --> 13:27.180
Ahmed's not blaming you.

13:27.220 --> 13:29.890
But everything's different now.

13:29.920 --> 13:32.420
Everything that I planned on.

13:34.290 --> 13:35.670
That's true,

13:35.700 --> 13:39.160
but we don't have
to talk about it yet.

13:39.190 --> 13:42.500
What do you mean?

13:42.530 --> 13:45.700
Why don't we take you home,
we get you better?

13:45.740 --> 13:48.900
No, tell me what it is that
we don't have to talk about yet.

13:55.650 --> 13:58.450
We're family.

13:58.480 --> 14:00.890
You're like a daughter to me.

14:00.930 --> 14:02.740
I mean that.

14:06.450 --> 14:09.220
But we're not
an ordinary family.

14:09.260 --> 14:12.560
We are the Al Fayeeds.

14:15.530 --> 14:18.530
My son will be president.

14:20.030 --> 14:22.130
And his son...

14:22.170 --> 14:25.090
will be president.

14:27.270 --> 14:29.780
A son that I cannot provide him.

14:29.810 --> 14:31.880
As much as Ahmed
loves you,

14:31.910 --> 14:34.610
he needs an heir.

14:34.650 --> 14:37.650
The people of Abuddin
need an heir.

14:37.680 --> 14:39.890
Especially now.

14:39.920 --> 14:42.710
And it's our job

14:42.750 --> 14:45.760
to do what's best
for the people.

14:45.790 --> 14:48.790
Does Ahmed know this?

14:52.100 --> 14:54.780
Not yet.

14:59.170 --> 15:01.370
But you'll convince him.

15:01.410 --> 15:04.440
You'll tell him
you're ending the marriage.

15:04.480 --> 15:06.440
For his sake.

15:06.480 --> 15:09.690
For the sake of Abuddin.

15:15.290 --> 15:19.790
Of course, we'll take care of
you wherever you decide to go.

15:19.820 --> 15:22.560
Anything you want,
anywhere you want.

15:22.590 --> 15:26.430
London, Paris, Dubai.

15:26.460 --> 15:30.520
You deserve... a life
outside of this place.

15:30.550 --> 15:33.850
It's taken far
too much from you.

15:41.240 --> 15:42.940
(grunting)

15:42.980 --> 15:45.440
This devil Khalil,

15:45.470 --> 15:46.910
he lived with you
for a month

15:46.940 --> 15:50.150
and you know nothing,
nothing about him, hmm?

15:50.190 --> 15:53.570
He stole your father's wife.

15:53.600 --> 15:55.050
He killed mine.

15:55.090 --> 15:56.920
ABU OMAR:
Ihab.

15:56.950 --> 16:00.390
- Nothing?
- Enough.

16:00.430 --> 16:03.680
Kasim's already told you
what he knows.

16:08.040 --> 16:09.800
Wait outside.

16:27.420 --> 16:28.870
You should take
three days.

16:28.910 --> 16:30.870
- I don't want three days.
- It's God's will.

16:30.910 --> 16:32.390
Hmm.

16:34.010 --> 16:36.620
As it was his will
to take Daliyah.

16:38.600 --> 16:41.620
Then it is God's will

16:41.660 --> 16:43.850
that I get my justice.

16:45.200 --> 16:47.370
You will have your justice.

16:47.410 --> 16:49.810
Already tonight,
we're rounding up the Christians

16:49.840 --> 16:51.110
and other apostates

16:51.140 --> 16:54.910
who we suspect are
supporting this man Khalil.

16:54.950 --> 16:58.620
"Christians."

16:58.650 --> 17:02.330
I want Khalil.

17:02.360 --> 17:05.609
OPERATOR: The number you
are calling has been disconnected.

17:09.260 --> 17:11.859
I finally talked to Ghani.

17:11.900 --> 17:15.230
Nasrin put him on the phone.

17:15.270 --> 17:16.900
He's good.

17:16.930 --> 17:18.930
He sounds good.

17:18.970 --> 17:21.670
He's not much
of a conversationalist.

17:21.700 --> 17:25.369
At least not with me.

17:25.410 --> 17:29.280
Maybe you'd be able
to get something out of him.

17:33.220 --> 17:34.780
What?

17:36.400 --> 17:39.420
It's Fauzi. Um...
I can't reach him. He...

17:39.450 --> 17:42.220
he's changed his number or...

17:43.420 --> 17:45.660
Sorry.
Tell me about Ghani.

17:47.030 --> 17:50.060
What good does it do
to call him?

17:50.100 --> 17:52.970
What if he's looking for her?

17:53.000 --> 17:55.270
Bassam.

17:55.300 --> 17:56.840
I want him to know.

17:56.870 --> 17:59.770
What?

17:59.810 --> 18:02.880
That you're sorry?

18:02.910 --> 18:07.010
That you need forgiveness?

18:07.050 --> 18:10.040
He won't be able
to give you that.

18:12.720 --> 18:15.290
I want him to know

18:15.320 --> 18:17.770
how hard she tried to be good

18:17.810 --> 18:21.090
and that no one
should ever judge her.

18:34.670 --> 18:37.440
I can't breathe.

18:41.310 --> 18:43.780
We just keep busy.

18:43.820 --> 18:47.520
We have things to do.

18:47.550 --> 18:49.620
HALIMA:
Khalil?

18:51.360 --> 18:54.160
Marwan is bringing someone
who wants to give us money.

18:54.190 --> 18:56.330
But he wants to meet you first.

18:56.360 --> 18:58.460
Who is it?

18:58.490 --> 19:01.060
Some rich kid from America.

19:02.430 --> 19:04.520
Don't worry.
If he doesn't checkout,

19:04.560 --> 19:06.070
we'll leave him there
rotting in the tunnel.

19:06.100 --> 19:07.740
(cell phone rings)

19:07.770 --> 19:09.450
It's Munir.

19:09.490 --> 19:10.820
Be careful.

19:10.850 --> 19:12.540
Always.

19:12.580 --> 19:13.980
You got my message.

19:14.010 --> 19:15.640
Yeah.

19:15.680 --> 19:19.020
Daliyah's safe here with us.

19:19.060 --> 19:20.200
Because of you.

19:20.240 --> 19:22.740
She's here because
of what you did.

19:24.750 --> 19:27.220
I'm glad.

19:27.260 --> 19:29.890
I am.

19:29.930 --> 19:32.730
But that woman who died...

19:32.760 --> 19:35.460
she was Ihab's wife.

19:35.500 --> 19:38.340
He is on a rampage.

19:40.370 --> 19:43.900
Just tell me you found a target.

19:43.940 --> 19:46.340
(indistinct chatter)

19:53.010 --> 19:56.590
Abu Omar is arresting
five families.

19:56.620 --> 20:00.000
Christian and other minorities
he thinks are supporting you.

20:00.040 --> 20:01.110
When's it happening?

20:01.140 --> 20:02.790
Tonight.

20:03.400 --> 20:06.500
That's enough time
to evacuate the families,

20:06.540 --> 20:08.130
set each house with explosives

20:08.160 --> 20:11.290
and detonate them once the
Caliphate soldiers are inside.

20:11.330 --> 20:12.760
You have the addresses?

20:12.800 --> 20:16.300
I had to get
into my brother's computer.

20:16.340 --> 20:19.200
He almost caught me.

20:19.240 --> 20:22.360
I don't think
I can do this anymore.

20:24.980 --> 20:28.380
Everything was normal last week.

20:28.410 --> 20:32.180
But it feels like ten years ago.

20:32.220 --> 20:34.850
Everyone's gone insane.

20:34.890 --> 20:37.490
My brother...

20:37.520 --> 20:40.290
he's not my brother anymore.

20:44.660 --> 20:46.370
(voice breaking):
It's like a nightmare,

20:46.400 --> 20:48.740
and I keep thinking
I'm going to wake up.

20:48.780 --> 20:51.340
- Hey, hey.
- (crying)

20:54.650 --> 20:56.010
It's okay.

20:56.050 --> 20:57.480
You'll be okay.

21:03.100 --> 21:05.100
♪

21:34.680 --> 21:36.330
Come on.

21:49.060 --> 21:50.290
Show me your hands.

21:50.320 --> 21:51.730
Keep them up unless
you want to die here.

21:51.760 --> 21:53.920
- Halima, it's me.
- Geez.

21:54.650 --> 21:56.590
- What...
- Hey, he's not armed.

21:56.630 --> 21:58.360
I used to be more trusting
than you, Marwan.

21:58.400 --> 21:59.620
Not anymore.

21:59.650 --> 22:01.410
He's got access to $10 million.

22:01.440 --> 22:02.830
Have you seen
this money?

22:02.870 --> 22:05.090
Not yet.
But I believe him.

22:05.120 --> 22:06.540
I need proof.

22:08.970 --> 22:10.610
Not until I see Abu Khalil.

22:10.640 --> 22:12.310
You don't make
the rules here.

22:14.580 --> 22:16.530
No weapon, but...

22:16.980 --> 22:18.950
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Hey, back off!

22:21.920 --> 22:25.390
I'm Sammy Al Fayeed.

22:42.890 --> 22:46.780
(birds singing)

22:46.780 --> 22:50.450
I haven't seen you here
since your father died.

22:50.490 --> 22:51.820
JAMAL:
No.

22:51.860 --> 22:53.660
You haven't.

22:53.690 --> 22:55.100
And your mother?

22:55.140 --> 22:56.830
How is she?

22:56.860 --> 23:00.900
I didn't come
to discuss my mother.

23:03.200 --> 23:05.700
He is punishing me.

23:05.740 --> 23:07.300
God.

23:07.340 --> 23:10.060
I keep praying for forgiveness,

23:10.090 --> 23:12.810
to end the punishment, but...

23:12.840 --> 23:14.610
Forgiveness?

23:14.640 --> 23:16.630
For what?

23:19.510 --> 23:22.980
Dooming Bassam,
my brother.

23:24.940 --> 23:27.320
This is why you believe
God is punishing you.

23:27.360 --> 23:29.660
What else
would you call

23:29.700 --> 23:32.360
losing half
the country,

23:32.390 --> 23:33.960
my grandson?

23:34.000 --> 23:35.410
Everything
that's happened,

23:35.440 --> 23:37.700
everything that
keeps happening...

23:37.730 --> 23:39.900
Is God's will.

23:41.170 --> 23:43.700
It's God's will, is it?

23:43.740 --> 23:46.150
Or is it because of me?

23:49.240 --> 23:51.430
There must be some way

23:51.460 --> 23:53.380
to end all of this.

23:53.410 --> 23:56.580
Because if not,
Ihab Rashid will come for us.

23:56.620 --> 23:59.580
For me,
my family.

23:59.620 --> 24:03.390
They will destroy us
and Abuddin will fall.

24:03.420 --> 24:07.570
Like Libya.
And I'm not Gaddafi.

24:10.260 --> 24:13.510
You won't destroy the threat
from outside the Palace

24:13.550 --> 24:16.330
until you deal with the threat
from within.

24:16.370 --> 24:18.770
From within?

24:18.800 --> 24:20.840
Yes.

24:23.940 --> 24:25.230
Are you saying

24:25.270 --> 24:27.560
someone inside
the Palace

24:27.590 --> 24:31.250
is working against me?

24:34.050 --> 24:37.090
The poison lies within.

24:43.530 --> 24:44.760
(door opens)

24:48.200 --> 24:49.660
Where have you been?

24:49.700 --> 24:51.900
I've been looking
for you.

24:51.940 --> 24:53.300
Nowhere.

24:53.340 --> 24:54.670
Here.

24:56.150 --> 24:58.020
Organizing these.

24:58.060 --> 25:00.050
There's so many boxes, you know?

25:00.090 --> 25:02.280
Too many to count.

25:02.310 --> 25:04.540
I've been here,
counting.

25:05.680 --> 25:07.190
Okay, well, count later.

25:07.220 --> 25:08.320
You're coming with me.

25:08.350 --> 25:10.000
Where?

25:10.030 --> 25:12.940
I've got us both
onto one of the arrest teams.

25:15.660 --> 25:18.290
But we're not on the roster.

25:18.330 --> 25:19.830
Abu Omar
assigned me.

25:20.160 --> 25:21.920
He felt bad about
Ihab pushing me around,

25:21.960 --> 25:25.670
so I asked him
if you could come, too.

25:29.000 --> 25:30.940
I-I can't.

25:30.970 --> 25:33.210
I need to finish these.

25:33.240 --> 25:35.640
And I need you to help me.

25:35.670 --> 25:37.210
Maybe we can go
on the next one.

25:37.240 --> 25:38.470
(laughing):
Yeah, no, thanks.

25:38.500 --> 25:41.590
Whatever we collect,
we get five percent.

25:43.280 --> 25:44.640
You can finish
off later.

25:44.670 --> 25:46.090
You're my brother
and you're helping me.

25:46.120 --> 25:47.720
Let's go. Come on.

25:59.460 --> 26:01.870
(indistinct conversations)

26:01.900 --> 26:04.030
Detonators are armed.

26:04.070 --> 26:06.100
Say when.

26:07.870 --> 26:10.110
They should be here soon.

26:20.690 --> 26:24.700
They marked
all the Christian houses.

26:24.730 --> 26:27.170
We grew up with the Christians.

26:27.210 --> 26:28.750
They were our friends.

26:28.790 --> 26:30.190
Our neighbors.

26:30.230 --> 26:33.530
We all got along, but now...

26:39.930 --> 26:41.900
Okay, here they come.

26:48.510 --> 26:49.760
Everyone on my team, let's go.

26:49.800 --> 26:51.880
Tum'a Street, number 42.

26:51.910 --> 26:54.320
(indistinct chatter)

27:07.290 --> 27:08.530
BARRY:
Shit.

27:08.560 --> 27:10.800
It's Munir and his brother.

27:11.430 --> 27:12.400
What the hell is Munir doing?

27:12.430 --> 27:13.970
He knows what
he's walking into.

27:14.000 --> 27:15.390
They're headed to number 42.

27:15.430 --> 27:16.700
Kill the detonator
for number 42.

27:16.730 --> 27:17.490
I can't.

27:17.520 --> 27:19.310
They're all
wired together.

27:19.340 --> 27:20.810
It's all of them
or none of them.

27:20.840 --> 27:22.880
Shit, shit.

27:22.910 --> 27:26.010
(chatter, shouting)

27:31.420 --> 27:33.920
We should stand down.

27:33.950 --> 27:35.070
Munir's our inside man.

27:35.100 --> 27:36.540
We need him.

27:39.210 --> 27:40.750
Khalil...

27:42.830 --> 27:45.160
No.

27:45.200 --> 27:48.540
If we don't do this,
we lose General Said.

27:49.900 --> 27:52.800
We can't defeat the Caliphate
without him.

27:56.210 --> 27:58.640
(panting)

28:02.500 --> 28:03.840
Here, the door. Go.

28:03.870 --> 28:05.350
(knocking at door)

28:05.380 --> 28:06.460
MAN:
Open up.

28:06.500 --> 28:08.840
This is the army
of the Caliphate.

28:08.870 --> 28:11.350
Come on!
(knocking continues)

28:11.440 --> 28:14.060
Open the door or...
[continues indistinctly]

28:14.100 --> 28:16.330
- Open the door!
- KASIM: Just break it down!

28:16.360 --> 28:18.460
Kasim... Kasim!

28:19.100 --> 28:21.260
This is the army
of the Caliphate.

28:21.260 --> 28:23.430
(panting):
I'm feeling sick.

28:23.430 --> 28:24.810
- Wait, wait, wait.
- They're almost inside.

28:24.840 --> 28:25.870
- They'll see it's wired.
- I know.

28:25.900 --> 28:26.970
I know. I'll tell you when.

28:27.000 --> 28:29.770
You've got a problem?

28:29.810 --> 28:30.770
Now.

28:30.810 --> 28:32.200
I put my neck on...

28:48.660 --> 28:50.490
(screaming)

28:50.530 --> 28:52.290
(screams)

28:52.330 --> 28:53.820
Kasim!

28:55.200 --> 28:57.130
Kasim...

29:04.400 --> 29:05.610
He's alive.

29:05.640 --> 29:07.540
Let's go.

29:07.580 --> 29:09.280
(panting)

29:09.310 --> 29:10.910
(men sobbing, groaning)

29:17.350 --> 29:18.880
REPORTER: Multiple bombs
killed at least 20

29:18.910 --> 29:21.680
Caliphate fighters in Ma'an
a little over an hour ago.

29:21.720 --> 29:22.740
Claiming credit for the attack

29:22.780 --> 29:24.590
was the man
known only as Khalil,

29:24.620 --> 29:26.120
whose Red Hand Brigade is waging

29:26.150 --> 29:28.100
an increasingly
lethal insurgency.

29:28.140 --> 29:30.220
Meanwhile, ba...

29:30.260 --> 29:31.600
This man.

29:31.640 --> 29:33.640
Khalil.

29:33.640 --> 29:36.210
He's the break
we've been waiting for.

29:36.240 --> 29:38.910
Once we meet, we can work
up a plan and retake Ma'an.

29:38.950 --> 29:42.570
With a man you neglected
to tell me about until now?

29:42.600 --> 29:44.120
We...

29:44.150 --> 29:47.050
<i>I</i> was being cautious.

29:47.090 --> 29:49.170
Before I involved you,
I had to test him.

29:49.210 --> 29:50.460
See if he was telling the truth.

29:50.490 --> 29:52.340
Yeah, and by doing so,

29:52.380 --> 29:56.740
we lost an opportunity
to kill Ihab Rashid.

29:56.780 --> 29:58.660
It would have been
a reckless decision.

29:58.700 --> 30:02.600
That decision was mine
to make, not yours.

30:05.200 --> 30:07.710
From now on, no more decisions

30:07.740 --> 30:09.770
without my consent.

30:09.810 --> 30:12.290
As for Khalil,
no one speaks to him

30:12.330 --> 30:14.140
but me.

30:14.180 --> 30:17.150
Mahmoud,
come with me.

30:17.180 --> 30:19.020
Father...

30:19.050 --> 30:20.350
(footsteps recede)

30:24.750 --> 30:26.250
You knew about this?

30:26.290 --> 30:28.010
Sir...

30:28.040 --> 30:29.960
General Said said
he would tell you.

30:29.990 --> 30:31.460
I thought he had.

30:31.490 --> 30:34.250
I swear it.

30:35.900 --> 30:37.900
You, I trust.

30:37.930 --> 30:39.870
With Rami, I'm...

30:39.900 --> 30:41.800
I'm not so
sure anymore.

30:41.830 --> 30:43.180
Hmm.

30:43.220 --> 30:44.870
He made a mistake.

30:44.910 --> 30:47.040
Maybe.

30:47.080 --> 30:49.720
Maybe I made a mistake

30:49.760 --> 30:52.010
to let him into the Palace.

30:52.050 --> 30:54.440
Maybe that Rashid
blood in him

30:54.470 --> 30:57.380
burns too hot.

30:57.420 --> 30:59.550
This man, Khalil...

30:59.590 --> 31:02.960
I want to talk
to him myself.

31:02.990 --> 31:04.690
- Yes, sir.
- Hmm.

31:06.930 --> 31:09.260
My advice?

31:09.300 --> 31:11.110
Get a jet.

31:11.150 --> 31:14.000
Gassed. On the runway.

31:14.030 --> 31:15.530
So you can escape this nightmare

31:15.570 --> 31:17.900
that you're about
to find yourself in.

31:17.940 --> 31:19.900
I have been here before.

31:19.930 --> 31:21.570
More than once.

31:23.380 --> 31:25.580
You will not even
get a chance

31:25.610 --> 31:28.250
to fire a shot
at the Caliphate

31:28.280 --> 31:30.080
before Jamal turns on you.

31:30.120 --> 31:32.480
He's my father.

31:33.620 --> 31:35.490
My family.

31:37.490 --> 31:39.520
Idi Amin,

31:39.560 --> 31:42.080
Baby Doc,

31:42.110 --> 31:45.330
Saddam Hussein.

31:45.360 --> 31:49.100
Family is always
the first to disappear.

31:52.810 --> 31:54.410
Hey.

31:54.440 --> 31:56.640
DALIYAH:
What took you so long?

31:56.670 --> 31:58.640
We, uh, we went north
before doubling back.

31:58.680 --> 31:59.990
Siddiq thought we
were being followed.

32:00.020 --> 32:00.940
I was wrong.

32:00.980 --> 32:02.450
Better to be
safe than sorry.

32:02.480 --> 32:04.180
It's all over the news.

32:04.220 --> 32:06.220
Come.

32:09.420 --> 32:12.020
The young man
Halima went to meet.

32:12.050 --> 32:13.060
Is she okay?

32:13.090 --> 32:15.660
She's fine, of course.

32:15.690 --> 32:18.330
I just...

32:18.360 --> 32:21.060
I don't know
how to say this.

32:21.100 --> 32:23.000
Say what?

32:24.670 --> 32:26.670
He is your son.

32:29.210 --> 32:31.340
My son?

32:31.370 --> 32:34.680
Yes.

32:34.710 --> 32:37.150
That's...

32:37.180 --> 32:39.150
that's impossible.

32:39.180 --> 32:42.650
Apparently not,
because he's here.

32:42.680 --> 32:43.590
Send him away.

32:43.630 --> 32:45.120
Tell Halima to get him
out of the city.

32:45.120 --> 32:47.330
He-he cannot be here.
He can't know who I am.

32:47.330 --> 32:50.190
I realize this isn't
how you intended this to happen.

32:50.230 --> 32:52.030
But he's come all this way

32:52.060 --> 32:53.760
and he's got the money
that we need.

32:53.790 --> 32:55.960
What money?
He doesn't have any money.

32:56.000 --> 32:58.240
Yes, he does.

32:59.100 --> 33:02.250
He inherited it when you died.

33:07.270 --> 33:08.750
You have been hiding

33:08.780 --> 33:11.840
since the moment
that we met.

33:11.880 --> 33:14.980
And now your son
has found you.

33:29.550 --> 33:32.550
♪

33:57.290 --> 33:58.730
I know a thousand things

33:58.770 --> 34:01.790
are going through
your head right now.

34:05.230 --> 34:08.659
Jamal promised to execute me.

34:12.170 --> 34:15.570
But he couldn't do it.

34:15.600 --> 34:19.139
So he left me for dead
in the desert.

34:19.179 --> 34:21.980
I barely survived.

34:22.010 --> 34:25.050
Walked for days
in the sun.

34:26.449 --> 34:28.650
And since everyone

34:28.679 --> 34:30.780
that I know and love

34:30.820 --> 34:32.489
thought I was dead...

34:34.219 --> 34:38.090
...I decided
to stay that way.

34:38.130 --> 34:40.659
I couldn't
hurt you again.

34:44.500 --> 34:46.469
Your letter...

34:46.500 --> 34:47.909
was the last thing I saw

34:47.949 --> 34:50.670
before they took me
from my cell.

34:53.070 --> 34:54.210
(yells)

34:54.239 --> 34:57.210
(grunting)

34:57.250 --> 34:59.210
No!

34:59.250 --> 35:01.650
No.
(grunting)

35:02.880 --> 35:04.580
Let go of me!

35:04.620 --> 35:09.170
Let go!
(sobbing)

35:25.040 --> 35:26.850
How long till we get the money?

35:28.250 --> 35:29.480
A day.

35:29.510 --> 35:31.420
Less if we're lucky.

35:31.450 --> 35:32.720
Sammy's not stupid.

35:32.750 --> 35:33.710
He's a smart kid.

35:33.710 --> 35:35.920
Yeah, well, smart kids
do stupid things.

35:35.950 --> 35:37.520
What he's doing,

35:37.520 --> 35:39.130
what he's done,
it's pretty admirable.

35:39.160 --> 35:41.150
Jim, it's not like he stole
the keys to my car.

35:41.190 --> 35:43.250
He's going to a war zone.

35:49.070 --> 35:50.870
I'm sorry.

35:52.570 --> 35:54.940
No, I understand.

35:56.650 --> 35:59.580
But we'll get
through this.

35:59.610 --> 36:01.040
Once Jamal releases
the money,

36:01.080 --> 36:02.790
I'll transfer it to
an offshore trust

36:02.820 --> 36:05.150
for this guy Khalil.

36:14.420 --> 36:18.230
It was either this or smoking.

36:19.430 --> 36:21.330
He'll call soon.

36:21.360 --> 36:23.380
Sammy will call, we'll
send him the money,

36:23.410 --> 36:25.770
and we'll all go home.

36:28.570 --> 36:31.910
You know there was
a memorial service, right?

36:36.640 --> 36:39.250
Never occurred to me
you weren't actually dead.

36:39.280 --> 36:42.330
Sammy, I couldn't
tell you the truth.

36:44.080 --> 36:46.090
Bullshit.

36:46.120 --> 36:47.650
Bullshit.

36:49.960 --> 36:52.860
I'm a man sentenced to death
for treason.

36:54.130 --> 36:56.930
They would never
let us be together.

36:56.960 --> 37:00.070
All I'd have ever
been to you was a...

37:00.100 --> 37:02.070
a voice

37:02.100 --> 37:04.670
hiding out
on the end of the phone.

37:04.700 --> 37:06.310
Yeah, well,
maybe I would've liked

37:06.310 --> 37:08.440
to hear your voice
one more time.

37:10.080 --> 37:12.440
Yeah, me, too.

37:15.110 --> 37:18.540
But that voice would've
kept you from moving on.

37:19.750 --> 37:21.720
And your mom...

37:21.750 --> 37:25.390
would never have
let herself be free.

37:28.530 --> 37:30.930
And so I chose silence.

37:32.830 --> 37:36.280
And if that was wrong,
then it was wrong

37:36.310 --> 37:39.440
out of love,
not from cowardice.

37:42.640 --> 37:44.710
Is that what you tell yourself?

37:46.710 --> 37:48.440
(sniffles)

37:49.950 --> 37:52.210
You know what
the weirdest part is?

37:52.250 --> 37:56.790
Seeing you right now
standing in front of me alive...

37:56.830 --> 37:59.860
should be a relief.

37:59.890 --> 38:02.860
It should make me happy, but...

38:02.890 --> 38:05.830
growing up,
you just kept pushing me away

38:05.860 --> 38:08.900
over and over again.

38:08.930 --> 38:12.600
Made me feel like there
was something wrong with me.

38:12.640 --> 38:15.790
I thought you secretly hated me.

38:18.170 --> 38:20.570
I thought I was
a disappointment.

38:22.780 --> 38:26.180
But now I-I realize
that I-I wasn't.

38:27.980 --> 38:30.380
You were.
(laughs)

38:30.420 --> 38:34.720
I guess I have more
to apologize for than I thought.

38:37.420 --> 38:39.830
I guess you do.

38:39.860 --> 38:42.010
Sammy, I love you.

38:45.010 --> 38:46.500
But this is a war zone.

38:46.530 --> 38:48.160
You have to go home.

38:49.040 --> 38:50.700
I'm not going home.

38:50.740 --> 38:52.730
I can't protect
you here.

38:52.770 --> 38:56.170
I'm not asking you
for your protection.

38:56.210 --> 38:59.210
I'm still your father.

38:59.240 --> 39:00.960
No, you're not.

39:01.000 --> 39:03.010
My father's dead.

39:03.050 --> 39:05.050
You're Abu Khalil.

39:05.080 --> 39:06.730
Remember?

39:09.630 --> 39:13.420
And I'm not gonna sit by
and watch men like me die.

39:17.520 --> 39:20.430
You've got a call.
It's urgent.

39:24.400 --> 39:27.010
Show Sammy where he can
sleep tonight.

39:28.710 --> 39:30.670
You need to get some rest.

39:35.240 --> 39:37.280
It's President Al Fayeed.

39:47.090 --> 39:50.560
BARRY:
Mr. President?

39:52.130 --> 39:53.660
This is Khalil,

39:53.700 --> 39:55.800
commander of the Red Hand.

39:55.830 --> 39:59.020
I did what General Said
asked me to.

39:59.060 --> 40:02.100
Now I'm hoping we can find
a way to work together.

40:02.140 --> 40:06.090
Yeah, well, first tell me
who you are.

40:06.380 --> 40:08.680
I told you...
my name is Khalil.

40:08.710 --> 40:12.250
Yes, but who are you really?

40:15.320 --> 40:18.650
I'm someone that can help you
defeat the Caliphate.

40:18.690 --> 40:20.270
That's all you need to know.

40:20.310 --> 40:21.550
Hmm.
(chuckles)

40:21.590 --> 40:24.060
I suppose you are right.

